  "text": "and February, 2017. Data from clinical history, CBC, serum biochemical profiles, echocardiograms, electrocardiograms, Holter monitors, and thoracic radiographs were collected by consultation with owners and referring cardiologists or internists. . [CITATION_1] 16 Normalized left ventricular internal diameter at end-diastole (LVIDdN) and 2D right parasternal short-axis LA-toaortic (LA:Ao) ratio were evaluated, with dilatation defined as LVIDdN > 1.73 and 2D LA:Ao > 1.5. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] 18 The presence and severity of valvular regurgitation and concurrent congenital or acquired cardiac defects were recorded.",
